      "span_text": "While such concerns emerged from studies that focused on pharmaceuticals, medical procedures and emerging biotechnologies, not much research has specifically examined 'hard' medical technologies, usually described as devices or equipment (i.e., ultrasound, radiotherapy, programmable intra-venous pumps)  .",
